We got the chicken shawarma and it was fantastic. Portions were big for a reasonable price. Def going back.
Bread was incredibly stale. Chicken and hummus good though.

(Translated by Google) Bit lost with so many options in the Time Out Market, just stopping at the Little Ada because I always liked the hummus tahini. We decided to try a different hummus and opted for the sweet potato. We bought two pita breads to go with it. The breads were fresh and warm, a delight to accompany the hummus, which was without doubt the best I have ever eaten. We ordered one portion only and it was more than enough for two people. When the bread was over and we went shopping he kindly gave us two more for nothing. Very polite and friendly. I'll be back there for sure!  (Original) Meio perdido com tantas opções dentro do Time Out Market, acabei parando no Little Ada porque sempre gostei de homus tahine. Resolvemos experimentar um homus diferente e optamos pelo de batata doce. Compramos dois pães pita para acompanhar. Os pães estavam frescos e aquecidos, uma delícia para acompanhar o homus, que foi sem dúvida o melhor que já comi. Pedimos uma porção apenas e foi mais do que suficiente para duas pessoas. Quando acabou o pão e fomos comprar mais ele gentilmente nos deu mais dois sem cobrar nada. Muito educado e simpático. Eu voltarei lá com certeza!
Best hummus I’ve ever hade. The market is an amazing vibe. The staff was super friendly and helpful!
Wow! The best hummus i ate in a while ! Highly recommended!

I ordered sabich and still am unsure of what I was served. Horribly spiced with missing ingredients for a dish that is certainly not what it’s supposed to be. Plus, everything was served very cold. Don’t waste your money- if you want Israeli food go to Breads Bakery stand next door.
Pretty good! Had the Chicken Shawarma, which came very fresh and quick. Although I have to say that I ate shawarma more aromatic and niftier, it was a very nice lunch for a very reasonable 16$.
